OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,FManchester Minshull Street Court heard
OL,7,Fthat Albie was struck in the garden
OL,8,Fwhile he played with the family's
OL,9,Fdogs, and was left with catastrophic
OL,10,Fhead injuries.
OL,12,FHe died in hospital some hours later,
OL,13,Fthe jury was told.
OL,15,FMr Speakman denies gross negligence
OL,16,Fmanslaughter in connection with the
OL,17,Flittle boy's death.
OL,19,FGiving evidence at his trial, he said:
OL,20,F"I shouldn't have to do this, it's
OL,21,Ff*****g not fair.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
