OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"I shouldn't have left him in the
OL,7,Fgarden, we all know that. I have not
OL,8,Fmet the standard of care. Is it truly
OL,9,Fexceptionally bad neglectful
OL,10,Fbehaviour? No. I messed up, I made a
OL,11,Fmistake."
OL,13,FProsecutor John Elvidge KC previously
OL,14,Fsaid the incident happened in a yard
OL,15,Fnext to a small garden at the front of
OL,16,Fthe house where Mr Speakman had left
OL,17,Fhis son to play.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/14
