OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,FThe court heard the machine was
OL,7,F'defective', as one of the wing
OL,8,Fmirrors was missing and the other was
OL,9,F"so dirty as to be useless".
OL,11,F"The prosecution case is that Albie
OL,12,Fdied as a result of his father's
OL,13,Fnegligence which created a serious and
OL,14,Fobvious risk of death, and the
OL,15,Fcircumstances of the breach by Neil
OL,16,FSpeakman of the duty of care which he
OL,17,Fowed his son were so exceptionally bad
OL,18,Fand reprehensible that the breach
OL,19,Famounts to gross negligence," Mr
OL,20,FElvidge previously said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/14
