OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,FGiving evidence, Mr Speakman broke
OL,7,Fdown in tears as he recounted the
OL,8,Fincident. He said Albie was dropped
OL,9,Foff by his mum in the morning before
OL,10,Fthey went to drop a woodchip delivery
OL,11,Foff in Burnley.
OL,13,FAfter they arrived home, the court
OL,14,Fheard Albie followed his dad to the
OL,15,Fback yard, either holding his hand or
OL,16,Fwalking next to him.
OL,18,FMr Speakman then began using the
OL,19,Ftelehandler to move some bags of the
OL,20,Fwoodchips, while Albie played, the
OL,21,Fjury heard.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/14
