OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"My intention was to reverse back and
OL,7,Fput the woodchip in the bags on the
OL,8,Fback, but that's when he was there,"
OL,9,FMr Speakman said.
OL,11,FHe said it was "second nature" to
OL,12,Fexaggerate looking as there was no
OL,13,Fmirror, so he would "profusely check
OL,14,Fthe blind spots".
OL,16,F"They need to know that I looked to
OL,17,Fsee if he was there, I knew to look
OL,18,Ffor him, I knew to look for my little
OL,19,Fboy.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/14
