OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"I'm careful with him, I'm always
OL,7,Fcareful in what I do. He was my little
OL,8,Fboy," he said, breaking down in tears.
OL,10,FAsked if he saw Albie, he said: "No, I
OL,11,Ffelt a bump, instantly. It felt like a
OL,12,Fhouse brick, I'd only gone back 10 or
OL,13,F20 centimetres. I felt a bump and
OL,14,Fthought 's***t, what's that?'.
OL,16,F"I stopped instantly, it was a split
OL,17,Fsecond, I looked right and saw his
OL,18,Ffeet. I jumped off. I shouldn't have
OL,19,Fto do this, it's f*****g not fair," Mr
OL,20,FSpeakman said in tears.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/14
