OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,FMr Speakman said he used the
OL,7,Ftelehandler between 200 and 300 times
OL,8,Fand was 'more than competent'. He said
OL,9,Fhe had 'no idea' there was no
OL,10,Freversing sound, or that the lights
OL,11,Fwere broken.
OL,13,FHe also said he would "exaggerate"
OL,14,Flooking over both shoulders to
OL,15,Feliminate blind spots and would turn
OL,16,Fhis body "almost 180 degrees" at least
OL,17,Ftwo to three times before moving.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/14
