OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"If I thought he was even an inch into
OL,7,Fthe yard I wouldn't have moved the
OL,8,Fvehicle," he said. "He was my little
OL,9,Fboy, if I thought for one second he
OL,10,Fwas not on the grass, I would not even
OL,11,Fhave moved that stupid thing."
OL,13,FIn cross examination, Mr Elvidge asked
OL,14,Fwhat Mr Speakman did to keep Albie
OL,15,Fsafe while he played outside. He
OL,16,Freplied: "I checked and checked again
OL,17,Fto make sure he wasn't."
OL,19,F"Why didn't you put him inside?," the
OL,20,Fprosecutor asked.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/14
