OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"He was three-years-old, it was 32
OL,7,Fdegrees, he wanted to play outside
OL,8,Fwith the dogs," Mr Speakman said.
OL,10,F"Do you want me to lock him in the
OL,11,Fhouse? Is that the world you live in?
OL,12,FWhy would I risk my son's f******
OL,13,Fsafety?."
OL,15,FMr Elvidge then referred back to his
OL,16,Fpolice interview, in which he told
OL,17,Fofficers: "He (Albie) knew, he weren't
OL,18,Ff****** stupid stupid. It's a farm
OL,19,Fisn't it? not a f****** playground and
OL,20,Fhe knows that.
