OL,3,CFarmer admits he 'messed up' over
OL,4,Cdeath of son by reversing over him
OL,6,F"He knows boundaries, he knows where
OL,7,Fto go and where not to go and what to
OL,8,Fgo near and what not to go f******
OL,9,Fnear."
OL,11,FThe prosecutor said: "He was three.
OL,12,FAre you suggesting that he was
OL,13,Fresponsible for managing his own risk?"
OL,15,FMr Speakman, of Bentley Hall Road,
OL,16,FTottington, Bury, denies gross
OL,17,Fnegligence manslaughter. He previously
OL,18,Fpleaded guilty to breaching a section
OL,19,Funder the Health and Safety at Work
OL,20,FAct 1974.
